Files in directories named "assets" are provided under the following terms of use:
(Original text: "BaseSystemEmptyData\ja-JP\others\素材規約.txt")

  - Image Assets: May be reused, modified, and used outside of WOLF RPG Editor.
    - However, you must include the creator's name when redistributing
      the enemy image assets created by GD as assets, whether unmodified or modified.
  - MIDI Assets: May be reused only.
  - WAV/OGG Assets: May be reused, modified, and used outside of WOLF RPG Editor.

    - "Reuse" refers to including the files in a game.
    - "Modify" refers to making changes to the files for use in your own game.

- Games using these assets may be sold.
  However, the sale of the assets themselves
  and any commercial use intended to provide them as assets is prohibited.

- "May be used outside of WOLF RPG Editor" means they may also be used for
  works created with other game engines. [Added on 01/28/2025]

- Bundling the sample game assets with self-made software for distribution is prohibited. [Added on 01/28/2025]
  However, users may download the sample game assets and use them
  in works created with such software (they may be used outside of WOLF RPG Editor).


Files in the "Extras\GraphicMaker\original" directory are provided under the following terms of use:
(Original text: "Extras\GraphicMaker\original\説明書・パーツ規格について.txt")

- Generated images may be used in both commercial and non-commercial works.
- Modification of generated images and part images is allowed.
  (Redistribution of the modified images is also allowed.)
- Redistribution of the part images is allowed.
  (However, commercial sale of the part images themselves is prohibited.)
- No name attribution is required in end credits or similar places.
- Use in tools other than WOLF RPG Editor is also allowed.


Other files may be modified and redistributed.
